sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT participant_id) AS num_participants
FROM responses
WHERE emotion_rating > (SELECT AVG(emotion_rating) FROM responses);

external_knowledge:
- 'resonated most deeply' refers to average emotion ratings and cognitive ratings greater than 5;
- 'beats of rock and roll' refers to the genre 'rocknroll';
- 'midpoint of the scale' refers to a rating scale from 1 to 10, where 5 is the midpoint.

- 'Dr. Johnson' is the name of the experimenter conducting the sessions;
- The session duration of more than 2 hours is calculated based on the difference between the end time and start time of the session;
- The emotional and cognitive ratings are on a scale from 1 to 10.

- A successful session is defined by the presence of a log entry with the note containing "successful" and the log type being "info";
- The emotional and cognitive ratings are on a scale from 1 to 10;
- The query focuses on sessions that were deemed successful, which implies a positive outcome or successful completion of the session.

sql:
SELECT AVG(emotion_rating) AS avg_emotion_rating, AVG(cognitive_rating) AS avg_cognitive_rating
FROM responses
WHERE trial_id IN (SELECT trial_id FROM trials WHERE session_id = 102);

external_knowledge:
- 'more experienced participants' refers to participants who have more years of music experience;
- 'particularly positive' refers to an average emotion rating greater than 5;
- 'age between 25 and 40' is the age range for the participants in this query.

- "seasoned musicians" refers to participants with more than 5 years of music experience;
- "deeply moved" refers to an average emotional rating greater than 7;
- "more intense trials" refers to trials with an onset time greater than 10 seconds and a duration greater than 5 seconds.
